    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-09-04T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-09-04T02:00:00-05:00" n="818"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d818">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/770: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-04T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 4, 1931—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 4—6:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>569. Department’s written instruction No. 550 of July 17.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>In comparing new draft with British draft we find that in article V the
                        words “or fine” after the words “for one year” (see British text telegraphed
                        April 19, 4 p.m.<note n="95" xml:id="d818fn95">See par. 3, subpar. (5), <ref
                                target="#pg_798">p. 798</ref>.</note>) have been dropped. Will
                        Department <pb facs="1022" n="912" xml:id="pg_912"/> inform me why these
                        words were dropped. They seemed to us necessary to make provisions
                        compatible with Chinese criminal code.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Why has Department dropped provision regarding court cases being heard in
                        Special Chambers from article VIII?</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Why were words “of any” after the words “the option” in second paragraph
                        of article No. XIV dropped?</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
